Right.
I want to make it very clear that I take Saddam Hussein to be a devil.

So we just go out and kill everybody around. It's a tragedy but
unavoidable. We have to do it, we can't help it. That's what history
demands. We carry the torch. We know better. Because we are the chosen
few. We shoulder the burden. Who differs in opinion is sadly deluded.
Sometimes we fail. Shit happens. But we are the final manifestation of
the world's development towards it's god-blessed good ends. Because we
are strong. Because we are good. God's own country. The safety and the
freedom of the planet depends on our friendly weapons. We just kill
the bad. Because we are the good. We are completely unselfish. We make
the whole world safe for democracy &amp;#8211; for the well-fare of all
people of this beautiful world. Any questions?

We can't organize a decent democratic election within our own country
but that's irrelevant.

There was a woman on CNN tonight, questioned: What do you think about
the war? &amp;#8211; Well, we gave them an ultimatum, they didn't comply,
so we have to strike back.

Sure, what else? Kill the bastards if they don't comply with our
demands. Nuke them. It's the Iraqui people's own fault. It's better
for the world. It will be a better world afterwards. Because we know
better, we are in the know. We have to defend the principles of the
free world. We are forced to do so by our ruthless enemies. Whatever
happens it's our enemies' fault. You object? Better be careful. What's
your name? We don't encourage dissenters. America, love it or leave
it.

I love it, so I left it.

Who the fuck are we?

I always wondered how facism in cultured Germany could become the
leading and self-distructive force. It's getting clearer to me now,
watching the developments inside the USA. You just need a basic trauma
( 9/11 in America - the lost WW I in Germany and the suffocating
war-penalties that unwisely strangulated German economies and violated
German self-respect ) &amp;#8211; and then you just need a few strong
people with their minds made up who bundle public anxieties and
understandable retaliation-dreams into three or four simple messages
and then you've got to get a real good deceitful propaganda department
like in the USSR and some real nice tricks to work your way round the
constitution, and there! look how the opposition in parliament is
crouching voluntarily and let's itself be kicked out of debate by
self-humiliation to the organized public discourse, and see how
smoothly parliament hands over it's democractic power and
responsibility as a blank check to the Leader, and you end up with the
Fuehrer's saying Â»Since 5.45 we are shooting backÂ« - meaning his
unprovoked military attack on Poland, for the well-fare of all the
good decent hard-working law-abiding people in the Third Reich. The
German people applauded widely ( not all of them, to their credit)
&amp;#8211; it was a relief-valve; and then there was no stopping anymore.
And more and more German people honestly thought that this was the
sensible solution to their national problems and fervently opposed any
idea that there was some evil lurking around in their own precincts.

Francis

